commit.message:
Add inline titles to the stats table columns

This aims to make this table somewhat more accessible to first-time
users who may not be familiar with what these names mean in cProfile
and are likely to be confused by the two "percall" columns.

Descriptions taken from the Stats Table section in the documentation.
Adds support for reusing TIME-WAIT sockets

Add note about profile data limitations

Links to https://github.com/jiffyclub/snakeviz/issues/112
as an explainer.

Closes #112

Use python -m snakeviz for starting snakeviz via magic

When starting snakeviz in the background for the ipython magic,
using sys.executable -m snakeviz will be less likely to run into
path issues than looking for the snakeviz executable.

Fixes #124

Add directory viewer to docs

Closes #109
Update changelog for version 2.0.1

Incorporate default ports for embedded rendering

Closes #125

Squashed commit of the following:

Author: Andrew Jones <andyjones.ed@gmail.com>

    Adds default ports for inline rendering, to improve usability through tunnels

Use document methods when setting up snakeviz iframe

jquery may not be available in all environments (notably jupyter lab),
so when setting up the snakeviz iframe it's best to use plain
DOM manipulation methods.
(jquery still gets loaded and used within the iframe.)

Fixes #123

Disable github edit link in mkdocs

Fixes #126

Update documentation link

Closes #127
Switch back to readable theme

Update documentation after v2.0.0 release

Documentation now reflects icicle as the default layout
and mentions Jupyter Notebook embedding.
Post release version bump to 2.1.dev
Updating change log

Explain Python version requirements on error

SnakeViz must be installed and run via the same version major
version (e.g. 2 or 3) of Python as was used to generate the
profile being displayed. This isn't always clear to people,
so this adds a note explaining this when there's an error
loading profile data via the pstats.Stats class.

Fixes #103

commit.message: Default to embedding snakeviz in notebooks
Use host 0.0.0.0 and update quoting.
Keep IPython optional for snakeviz usage

Add -e/--embed option to snakeviz magic

So that if the user is running the SnakeViz magic in the
notebook they can choose to have it embedded instead of
opened in a new tab.

1. Wait the loading of browser until the snakeviz cli has finished initialize, much more robust than `sleep(0.5)`
2. Change the notebook html template to have id starts with "snakeviz-"
3. Resolve concern from @jiffyclub #110
Install ipython to make test right
Check if %snakeviz magic is running in jupyter notebook, then embed the visualization inside the notebook as a html cell #58 #88
